{"title_page": "Original Single Kollektion", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Original Single Kollektion\n| type         = compilation\n| artist       = [[Rammstein]]\n| cover        = Original_single_kollektion.jpg\n| released     = 19 July 1998\n| recorded     = 1994\u20131997\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Neue Deutsche H\u00e4rte]], [[industrial metal]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Motor Music Records|Motor]]\n| producer     = [[Jacob Hellner]] with [[Rammstein]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Original Single Kollektion''' ({{lang-en|Original Single Collection|italic=yes}}) is a compilation album limited to 10,000 copies, released by German [[Neue Deutsche H\u00e4rte]] band [[Rammstein]]. It was released in July 1998 and contains the first 6 [[Single (music)|singles]] of the band, as well as a poster. The cover art of the box set is similar to the [[Coat of arms of the German Democratic Republic|East German coat of arms]].\n\n== Track listing ==\n=== Du riechst so gut ===\n#[[Du riechst so gut]] (Single Version) - 4:50\n#Wollt ihr das Bett in Flammen sehen? - 5:19\n#Du riechst so gut (Scal Remix) - 4:45\n\n=== Seemann ===\n#[[Seemann (Rammstein song)|Seemann]] - 4:48\n#Der Meister - 4:10\n#Rammstein in the House ([[Jean F. Cochois|Timewriter]] Rmx) - 6:24\n\n=== Engel ===\n#[[Engel (song)|Engel]] - 4:23\n#Sehnsucht - 4:02\n#Rammstein (Eskimos & Egypt Radio Edit) - 3:41\n#Rammstein (Eskimos & Egypt Instrumental Edit) - 3:27\n#Rammstein - 4:25\n\n=== Engel (Fan-Edition) ===\n#[[Engel (song)#Track listings|Engel (Extended Version)]] - 4:34\n#Feuerr\u00e4der (Live Demo Version 1994) - 4:47\n#Wilder Wein (Demo Version 1994) - 5:41\n#Rammstein (Eskimos & Egypt Instrumental) - 3:27\n\n=== Du hast ===\n#[[Du hast]] - 3:54\n#B\u00fcck dich - 3:21\n#Du hast (Remix by [[Jacob Hellner]]) - 6:44\n#Du hast (Remix by [[Clawfinger]]) - 5:24\n\n=== Das Modell ===\n#[[Das Model#Cover versions|Das Modell]] - 4:46\n#Kokain - 3:09\n#Alter Mann (Special Version) - 4:22\n#''Rammstein Computerspiel f\u00fcr Windows <small>(video game for [[Windows]])</small>''\n\n==Personnel==\n===Rammstein===\n* [[Till Lindemann]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* [[Richard Z. Kruspe]] \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Paul Landers]] \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Oliver Riedel]] \u2013 bass guitar\n* [[Christoph Schneider]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n* [[Christian Lorenz|Christian \"Flake\" Lorenz]] \u2013 keyboards, [[Sampler (musical instrument)|samples]], synthesizers\n{{Rammstein}}\n\n[[Category:Rammstein albums]]\n[[Category:1998 compilation albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Original Single Kollektion\n| type         = compilation\n| artist       = [[Rammstein]]\n| cover        = Original_single_kollektion.jpg\n| released     = 19 July 1998\n| recorded     = 1994\u20131997\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Neue Deutsche H\u00e4rte]], [[industrial metal]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Motor Music Records|Motor]]\n| producer     = [[Jacob Hellner]] with [[Rammstein]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Original Single Kollektion''' ({{lang-en|Original Single Collection|italic=yes}}) is a compilation album limited to 10,000 copies, released by German [[Neue Deutsche H\u00e4rte]] band [[Rammstein]]. It was released in July 1998 and contains the first 6 [[Single (music)|singles]] of the band, as well as a poster. The cover art of the box set is similar to the [[Coat of arms of the German Democratic Republic|East German coat of arms]].\n\n== Track listing ==\n=== [[Du riechst so gut]] ===\n#Du riechst so gut <small> (Single Version) </small> - 4:50\n#Wollt ihr das Bett in Flammen sehen? - 5:19\n#Du riechst so gut <small> (Scal Remix) </small> - 4:45\n\n=== [[Seemann (Rammstein song)|Seemann]] ===\n#Seemann - 4:48\n#Der Meister - 4:10\n#Rammstein in the House <small> (Timewriter Rmx) </small> - 6:24\n\n=== [[Engel (song)|Engel]] ===\n#Engel - 4:23\n#Sehnsucht - 4:02\n#Rammstein <small> (Eskimos & Egypt Radio Edit) </small> - 3:41\n#Rammstein <small> (Eskimos & Egypt Instrumental Edit) </small> - 3:27\n#Rammstein - 4:25\n\n=== [[Engel (song)|Engel (Fan-Edition)]] ===\n#Engel <small> (Extended Version) </small> - 4:34\n#Feuerr\u00e4der <small> (Live Demo Version 1994) </small> - 4:47\n#Wilder Wein <small> (Demo Version 1994) </small> - 5:41\n#Rammstein <small> (Eskimos & Egypt Instrumental) </small> - 3:27\n\n=== [[Du hast]] ===\n#Du hast - 3:54\n#B\u00fcck dich - 3:21\n#Du hast <small> (Remix by [[Jacob Hellner]]) </small> - 6:44\n#Du hast <small> (Remix by [[Clawfinger]]) </small> - 5:24\n\n=== [[Das Model]]l ===\n#Das Modell - 4:46\n#Kokain - 3:09\n#Alter Mann <small> (Special Version) </small> - 4:22\n#Rammstein Computerspiel f\u00fcr Windows <small>(video game for [[Windows]])</small>\n\n==Personnel==\n===Rammstein===\n* [[Till Lindemann]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* [[Richard Z. Kruspe]] \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Paul Landers]] \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n* [[Oliver Riedel]] \u2013 bass guitar\n* [[Christoph Schneider]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n* [[Christian Lorenz|Christian \"Flake\" Lorenz]] \u2013 keyboards, [[Sampler (musical instrument)|samples]], synthesizers\n{{Rammstein}}\n\n[[Category:Rammstein albums]]\n[[Category:1998 compilation albums]]\n", "name_user": "Urgal", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTrack listing:original track names", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Original_Single_Kollektion"}
